### Description

Hello, I have just migrated my whole project to standalone components. In general, my project is designed as a single module - single component, but modules sometimes also provide services/other singleton dependencies. I also extensively use lazy modules (not router ones - loaded manually with `loadChildren`).

The compilation has the same output (files out, ~their size), but in total it is about 20-30% slower than earlier; I checked it a couple of times, also go back in the history before change and to the current state; it was reproductive. It is a production app.

The question is whether you noticed similar behavior, are some changes are expected or possible, to optimize it.
I am also using nrwl, but as mentioned - the difference is visible between migration to standalone components commits and multiple repetitions of builds.

